WHO   — Father Francis McKeen — the abuser, judged
WHAT  — The cruelty the gentle man absorbed: the human evil that makes Jobe's later wrath legible, if not clean.
WHERE — LMM · The Lawnmower Man (1992)  Framework inputs: The Lawnmower Man (1992, dir. Brett Leonard, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the fear curdles faster when the awakened tool has real wounds to avenge.
HOW   — By abusing Jobe under the cover of care, then meeting the power he helped create.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I told him God was watching and I raised my hand to him anyway. I am the cruelty that taught the gentle man what wrath was for.

